## shadcn/ui Component Library Structure Report

Based on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's everything you need to know to add a new component to the shadcn/ui library:

---

### 1. TOP-LEVEL DIRECTORY STRUCTURE

```
/
├── apps/
│   └── v4/                          # Main demo/docs application (Next.js)
│       ├── app/                     # Next.js app directory
│       ├── registry/                # All components organized by style
│       │   ├── new-york-v4/        # Primary style/registry
│       │   ├── bases/              # Base component definitions
│       │   ├── blocks/             # Complex component compositions
│       │   └── ...other styles
│       ├── lib/                     # Shared utilities and helpers
│       ├── hooks/                   # Custom React hooks
│       ├── components/              # Internal app components
│       ├── styles/                  # Global styles
│       ├── registry.json            # Generated registry manifest
│       └── components.json          # shadcn/ui config file
├── packages/
│   ├── shadcn/                      # Main CLI tool package
│   │   └── src/
│   │       ├── registry/            # Registry API and logic
│   │       ├── schema/              # Zod schemas for validation
│   │       ├── commands/            # CLI commands
│   │       └── utils/
│   └── tests/
├── templates/                       # Boilerplate for projects
├── scripts/                         # Build and utility scripts
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml             # Monorepo configuration
```

---

### 2. HOW EXISTING COMPONENTS ARE ORGANIZED

Components follow a standard pattern. Here's the structure for a style (e.g., `new-york-v4`):

```
registry/new-york-v4/
├── ui/                    # Component definitions
│   ├── accordion.tsx      # Component file
│   ├── dialog.tsx
│   ├── tabs.tsx
│   ├── alert.tsx
│   └── _registry.ts       # Registry metadata for all UI components
├── examples/              # Usage examples
│   ├── accordion-demo.tsx
│   ├── tabs-demo.tsx
│   └── _registry.ts       # Registry metadata for all examples
├── blocks/                # Complex pre-built compositions
│   └── dashboard-01/
├── charts/                # Chart components
├── hooks/                 # Custom hooks
├── lib/                   # Style-specific utilities
├── internal/              # Internal/hidden components
└── registry.ts            # Main registry aggregator
```

---

### 3. COMPOUND COMPONENT EXAMPLES

#### Example 1: Accordion (Compound with Context-like Pattern)

**File:** `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/accordion.tsx`

```typescript
"use client"

import * as React from "react"
import { ChevronDownIcon } from "lucide-react"
import { Accordion as AccordionPrimitive } from "radix-ui"

import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

function Accordion({
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<typeof AccordionPrimitive.Root>) {
  return <AccordionPrimitive.Root data-slot="accordion" {...props} />
}

function AccordionItem({
  className,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<typeof AccordionPrimitive.Item>) {
  return (
    <AccordionPrimitive.Item
      data-slot="accordion-item"
      className={cn("border-b last:border-b-0", className)}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}

